reviewText: Interesting film about family and the impact of prejudice.

Funny! Touching! Powerful social commentary! Important spiritual message regardless of the faith one practices. Sad lesson about bigotry! Reminder of family connections. Good stuff! Very enjoyable and meaningful.
Interesting, fun movie, good watch for relaxing weekend night.

I watched this to practice my French, and didn't expect more than light entertainment, but this was a lovely humanistic movie that went beyond the sit-com I was expecting. Even the small parts were three-dimensional. There were lots of well-done small moments, and wonderful warm humor throughout. It didn't insult the viewer's intelligence. Well worth watching.

How one can see oneself and how others can see you if they believe you are from one country(Italy) and not from another(Algeria). Despite all the efforts one can made to conceal one true's identity, at the end,  it is more important to be TRUE to oneself. The Truth will set one free for sure.
Don't waste your time on this film.
great plot and cast! loved it!!!
Got boring quickly.  Just didn't "make it".
Kad Merad at his best!  I love this movie!  it is funny and it deals with the subject of immigration in a amusing and sensitive way!  But, most of all; the film is funny!
Very engaging movie about racism and bigotry and one man's acceptance of who he is in spite of the blowback from society.

What can I say about Kad Merad that probably hasn't already been said. He is fantastic, heartfelt, warm, and knows how to captivate. This movie played a close part to my heart. Being a Muslim American (Persian/American) born and raised in the states, this really hit home. It took me back to my religious roots and left me thinking days after. Would def recommend and watch over and over again.
